01:55:16,883 --> 01:55:20,385
"paid proper like...
it'd be a lot easier, but..."

1398
01:55:22,485 --> 01:55:24,504
But it's been paid for...

1399
01:55:24,863 --> 01:55:31,861
"Yeah, but, in the freight industry
carrying dangerous load it cost more."

1400
01:55:33,662 --> 01:55:36,140
"A surcharge, they call it."

1401
01:55:37,166 --> 01:55:43,230
"If this were a professional job,
I could just charge you."

1402
01:55:45,632 --> 01:55:48,443
"But Ben, I don't have any more money."

1403
01:55:53,515 --> 01:55:56,242
"Oh, that's no good then."

1404
01:56:00,271 --> 01:56:07,187
"You said once, you said once, that there
aren't many pleasures in my life."

1405
01:56:10,448 --> 01:56:13,676
"And you know,
I go to Miss Laura once a week."

1406
01:56:14,994 --> 01:56:21,802
And you got me to see that it weren't
nothing to be ashamed of.

1407
01:56:26,673 --> 01:56:29,566
I was gonna go there tonight...

1408
01:56:31,968 --> 01:56:35,947
and of course it costs me.

1409
01:56:37,683 --> 01:56:42,036
"I mean, not as much as..."

1410
01:56:43,772 --> 01:56:51,112
"not as much as a surcharge
for dangerous goods, but still..."

1411
01:56:54,323 --> 01:56:56,425
"it does cost me, you know."

1412
01:56:57,034 --> 01:56:59,803
"No, Ben, no... please don't..."

1413
01:57:00,246 --> 01:57:04,641
"It's not personal, Grace.
It's not personal. I just..."

1414
01:57:06,293 --> 01:57:09,187
"I have to take due payment, that's all."

1415
01:57:10,005 --> 01:57:13,233
I don't...
I don't have a choice.

1416
01:57:14,009 --> 01:57:17,320
I can't buck the freight
in this big craft.

1417
01:57:20,765 --> 01:57:26,537
We're parked in the square in Georgetown.
Right outside the church.

1418
01:57:27,772 --> 01:57:30,041
You'd better keep your voice down.

1419
01:57:34,111 --> 01:57:35,779
"No, Ben..."

1420
01:57:35,780 --> 01:57:41,594
"This ain't somethin' I'm proud of, Grace.
Don't go thinking that."

1421
01:58:14,275 --> 01:58:17,083
"Grace fell asleep on the long highway,"

1422
01:58:17,084 --> 01:58:22,575
"thanks to her healthy ability to push
any unpleasantness around her far away."

1423
01:58:22,576 --> 01:58:27,846
"A generous God had blessed her with the
rare talent of being able to look ahead,"

1424
01:58:28,205 --> 01:58:30,307
and only ahead.

1425
01:58:31,792 --> 01:58:36,027
"And later when the truck slowed
down about to reach its destination"

1426
01:58:36,028 --> 01:58:38,714
"and she slowly returned
to consciousness,"

1427
01:58:38,715 --> 01:58:42,384
she had no way of knowing
how long she had slept.

1428
01:58:42,385 --> 01:58:47,365
All she knew was that she would be
happy to see the light of day again.

1429
01:58:49,767 --> 01:58:52,328
And then she heard the dog.

1430
01:58:58,025 --> 01:59:01,630
All your fondness for apples seems
less and less believable.

1431
01:59:02,363 --> 01:59:03,923
You've bruised 'em.

1432
01:59:16,668 --> 01:59:19,771
We had a meeting last night
at the mission house.

1433
01:59:22,048 --> 01:59:25,467
"They said you might be
going to try to run away,"

1434
01:59:25,468 --> 01:59:30,156
"so when I discovered you'd hidden
yourself away on my truck,"

1435
01:59:31,475 --> 01:59:34,952
I didn't have no choice but
to bring you back to Dogville.

1436
01:59:36,605 --> 01:59:39,665
In the freight industry
we can't take sides.

1437
02:00:23,900 --> 02:00:27,207
"It didn't help Grace that the
first theft ever registered in Dogville"

1438
02:00:27,208 --> 02:00:29,070
"had taken place
the previous evening,"

1439
02:00:29,071 --> 02:00:33,509
when most people were assembled
for the town meeting.

1440
02:00:33,867 --> 02:00:36,698
Old Tom Edison Senior
had a considerable sum

1441
02:00:36,699 --> 02:00:39,288
of money stolen
from his medicine closet

1442
02:00:39,289 --> 02:00:41,874
"and suspicion soon fell on Grace,"

1443
02:00:41,875 --> 02:00:46,980
who had apparently been planning an escape
that would surely require funding.

1444
02:00:47,255 --> 02:00:51,818
Grace chose to remain silent
in the face of these new charges.

1445
02:00:53,094 --> 02:00:57,253
"And then Bill, who had lately
improved his engineering skills"

1446
02:00:57,254 --> 02:00:59,168
"to an astonishing degree,"

1447
02:00:59,309 --> 02:01:02,316
"had, by way of his first
design, implemented"

1448
02:01:02,317 --> 02:01:04,966
"a kind of
escape prevention mechanism."

1449
02:01:05,273 --> 02:01:11,337
"Beautiful it might not have been,
but effective he dared say it was."

1450
02:01:22,289 --> 02:01:26,852
"Grace, we don't like having to do this."

1451
02:01:27,544 --> 02:01:32,399
We don't have much of a choice
if we are to protect our community.

1452
02:01:32,632 --> 02:01:37,028
Could you... Do you mind moving?
Try moving.

1453
02:01:57,156 --> 02:01:58,382
It works.

1454
02:01:59,491 --> 02:02:05,931
We had to make this heavy enough so that
it can only move where the ground's level.

1455
02:02:05,998 --> 02:02:09,476
And the ground is level in town.

1456
02:02:14,589 --> 02:02:16,649
May I go now?

1457
02:02:22,306 --> 02:02:25,908
I have to figure out
how I'm going to get into my house.

1458
02:02:27,977 --> 02:02:31,747
"Or is that part of the punishment,
having to sleep outdoors?"

1459
02:02:32,106 --> 02:02:34,774
"No, no no Grace."

1460
02:02:34,775 --> 02:02:39,046
Don't think of this as punishment.
Not at all!

1461
02:02:39,947 --> 02:02:45,135
"Bill, he made the chain long enough
so that you can sleep in your bed."

1462
02:02:56,046 --> 02:02:57,689
"Grace, six o'clock."

1463
02:03:00,884 --> 02:03:03,278
"Yes, Mrs. Henson."

1464
02:03:31,872 --> 02:03:34,206
I couldn't run the risk
of Dad turning me down.

1465
02:03:34,207 --> 02:03:37,060
"But, they think it was
me that took the money."

1466
02:03:37,878 --> 02:03:40,021
'Cause I told them so.

1467
02:03:44,008 --> 02:03:45,944
You did what?

1468
02:03:46,511 --> 02:03:49,638
"First they suspected me, but then
I convinced them that it was you,"

1469
02:03:49,639 --> 02:03:52,491
since you were the one
using the medicine closet.

1470
02:03:53,851 --> 02:03:54,869
Why?

1471
02:03:55,312 --> 02:03:57,229
Because I'm here to do
the thinking for you.

1472
02:03:57,230 --> 02:04:01,667
"If we are to have the slightest
chance of getting you out of here,"

1473
02:04:02,902 --> 02:04:05,879
they can never know how
close we really are.

1474
02:04:07,406 --> 02:04:11,093
They can't know I'm trying to help you.

1475
02:04:13,161 --> 02:04:15,376
"If they knew it was me
that took the money,"

1476
02:04:15,377 --> 02:04:17,442
"I wouldn't be here
talking to you now."

1477
02:04:20,335 --> 02:04:22,979
"Please don't disappear, Tom."

1478
02:04:28,885 --> 02:04:30,695
I need you.

1479
02:04:33,681 --> 02:04:37,201
I'll break this one...
with some thinking.

1480
02:04:47,152 --> 02:04:51,104
"It was not Grace's pride
that kept her going during the days"

1481
02:04:51,105 --> 02:04:54,700
"when fall came and the trees
were losing their leaves,"

1482
02:04:54,701 --> 02:04:58,317
"but more of the trance-like state
that descends on animals"

1483
02:04:58,318 --> 02:05:00,080
"whose lives are threatened,"

1484
02:05:00,081 --> 02:05:04,460
"a state in which the body reacts
mechanically, in a low, tough gear,"

1485
02:05:04,461 --> 02:05:07,546
without too much painful reflection.

1486
02:05:07,547 --> 02:05:12,318
Like a patient passively letting
his disease hold sway.

1487
02:05:13,262 --> 02:05:17,892
"And now that Vera had received proof
that it was in fact Chuck..."

1488
02:05:17,893 --> 02:05:20,767
"who'd forced his attentions on Grace,"

1489
02:05:20,768 --> 02:05:23,204
she was meaner than ever.

1490
02:05:26,482 --> 02:05:32,087
"Had Grace had friends in Dogville they,
too, fell like the leaves."

1491
02:05:33,572 --> 02:05:38,298
The most towns-people of the male sex
now visited Grace at night

1492
02:05:38,299 --> 02:05:40,647
to fulfill their sexual needs.

1493
02:05:41,955 --> 02:05:44,915
It had occurred to the children
to give the bell an extra ring

1494
02:05:44,916 --> 02:05:50,647
"every time such an act had been
consummated, much to Martha's confusion."

1495
02:05:52,674 --> 02:05:57,737
But since the chain had been attached
things had become easier for everyone:

1496
02:05:59,139 --> 02:06:02,974
"the harassment in bed did not have to be
kept so secret anymore,"

1497
02:06:02,975 --> 02:06:06,644
because they couldn't really be
compared to a sexual act.

1498
02:06:06,645 --> 02:06:11,608
"They were embarrassing in the way it is
when a hillbilly has his way with a cow,"

1499
02:06:11,609 --> 02:06:13,168
but no more than that.

1500
02:06:15,113 --> 02:06:17,029
Tom saw everything.

1501
02:06:17,030 --> 02:06:22,469
"It pained him, and the sexual visits
were a particularly severe blow."

1502
02:06:29,126 --> 02:06:34,588
"But he supported her as best he could,
the way a spider supports,"

1503
02:06:34,589 --> 02:06:38,401
when it has been tangled
in its own web by the wind.

1504
02:06:39,343 --> 02:06:40,528
Tom!

1505
02:06:47,309 --> 02:06:50,287
Everything I tried to do went wrong.

1506
02:06:51,313 --> 02:06:54,649
I can't come up with the answer
I was looking for.

1507
02:06:54,650 --> 02:06:59,504
"You'll come up with it, you'll see.
You're very clever."

1508
02:07:01,032 --> 02:07:06,137
- We provoked them.
- I wouldn't worry about it.

1509
02:07:11,083 --> 02:07:12,145
We provoked them.

1510
02:07:12,146 --> 02:07:15,002
Now it is time for us
to provoke ourselves.

1511
02:07:15,003 --> 02:07:16,295
What do you mean?

1512
02:07:16,296 --> 02:07:21,134
"I mean, by showing them some trust."

1513
02:07:21,135 --> 02:07:25,613
"It all started with a meeting, so it
will be logical to end it with one, too."

1514
02:07:25,763 --> 02:07:30,075
You'll talk and they'll listen.
They can't refuse to listen.

1515
02:07:32,020 --> 02:07:33,158
What will I say?

1516
02:07:33,159 --> 02:07:35,772
Everything.
You'll say everything.

1517
02:07:35,773 --> 02:07:36,645
"Everything?"

1518
02:07:36,646 --> 02:07:38,691
"Yeah, the truth. The Truth."

1519
02:07:38,692 --> 02:07:41,360
Just the truth about each and
every one of them.

1520
02:07:41,361 --> 02:07:43,613
I don't think they are
gonna want to hear that.

1521
02:07:43,614 --> 02:07:49,761
"I know, I know. It is like a child
who doesn't want to take his medicine."

1522
02:07:51,080 --> 02:07:54,092
"They'll be furious at first,
but in the end"

1523
02:07:54,093 --> 02:07:56,667
"they'll see it is for their own good."

1524
02:07:56,668 --> 02:08:00,646
Just don't be hateful.
Don't be reproving.

1525
02:08:01,839 --> 02:08:04,567
"If anybody can do it,
Grace, you can."

1526
02:08:05,259 --> 02:08:10,127
They'll all realize that this weapon
and this understanding and injustice

1527
02:08:10,128 --> 02:08:12,918
has only one true victim
and that's you.

1528
02:08:13,059 --> 02:08:16,954
And from there it is only
one small step to forgiveness.

1529
02:08:18,023 --> 02:08:23,252
"You've done some hard
thinking, Tom Edison."

1530
02:08:23,902 --> 02:08:28,840
I'm sure it is an excellent plan.
I'm sure.

1531
02:08:48,134 --> 02:08:51,510
"If forgiveness was close at hand
in the mission house,"

1532
02:08:51,511 --> 02:08:53,499
"they were all hiding it well."

1533
02:08:54,849 --> 02:08:57,785
It hadn't been easy for Tom
to get them there.

1534
02:08:58,227 --> 02:09:04,374
Appealing to consciences stowed farther
and farther away by their owners every day

1535
02:09:04,399 --> 02:09:08,909
"as if they were as fragile as
Henson's glasses after polishing,"

1536
02:09:08,910 --> 02:09:10,849
"had proved quite a task."

1537
02:09:11,406 --> 02:09:15,409
"But if one was going, the others
might as well come along, too,"

1538
02:09:15,410 --> 02:09:18,346
so nobody could talk
behind anybody's back.

1539
02:09:20,415 --> 02:09:23,977
Tom had set the scene for Grace's speech.

1540
02:09:24,252 --> 02:09:29,899
"Now she'd have to sink or swim,
and sincerity be brought to bear."

1541
02:09:31,551 --> 02:09:34,319
While Grace addressed
the silent congregation

1542
02:09:34,320 --> 02:09:36,388
in the mission house on Elm Street

1543
02:09:36,389 --> 02:09:40,701
the first of the early autumn snowstorms
embraced the town.

1544
02:09:41,185 --> 02:09:44,925
The snowflakes dusted down
over the old buildings

1545
02:09:44,926 --> 02:09:47,634
as if this were just any old town.

1546
02:09:47,901 --> 02:09:52,087
"And they played in the branches and twigs
from which the apples had hung,"

1547
02:09:52,112 --> 02:09:54,001
but luckily the harvest was home

1548
02:09:54,002 --> 02:09:56,908
and via the freight industry
had found a market

1549
02:09:56,909 --> 02:10:00,178
despite the ever disappointing prices.

1550
02:10:00,328 --> 02:10:03,288
Grace had presented
her story with clarity.

1551
02:10:03,289 --> 02:10:06,416
She had not embellished or understated.

1552
02:10:06,417 --> 02:10:11,606
"And just as she finished the snowflakes
all at once stopped tumbling down,"

1553
02:10:12,298 --> 02:10:19,222
"leaving Dogville clad in the daintiest,
whitest blanket of snow imaginable."

1554
02:10:38,240 --> 02:10:40,592
I don't think it went very well.

1555
02:10:40,700 --> 02:10:43,678
It's fine. You did good.

1556
02:10:51,627 --> 02:10:56,315
"The snow had come early,
perhaps too early."

1557
02:10:56,340 --> 02:10:59,777
A misplaced augury of conciliation.

1558
02:11:00,720 --> 02:11:03,555
"Tom looked around, worried:"

1559
02:11:03,556 --> 02:11:07,642
Vera's teeth were clenched.
She was the first to speak.

1560
02:11:07,643 --> 02:11:10,311
Copious lies. Just lies.

1561
02:11:10,312 --> 02:11:13,196
"Yes, Tom. It doesn't accord
with the perceptions I got"

1562
02:11:13,197 --> 02:11:15,010
"of this town and
its residents."

1563
02:11:15,734 --> 02:11:19,737
"I'm a doctor, damn it, I don't need
anyone to tell me if I'm sick or not."

1564
02:11:19,738 --> 02:11:21,923
"What do you have to say
for yourself, Tom?"

1565
02:11:22,032 --> 02:11:24,426
Maybe it's time you picked sides!

1566
02:11:24,951 --> 02:11:27,244
Are you for us or against us?

1567
02:11:27,245 --> 02:11:30,163
Liz is right. We've been
far too indulgent with Tom.

1568
02:11:30,164 --> 02:11:33,976
"Tom, I got to tell you.
Even I have trouble defending that girl."

1569
02:11:34,419 --> 02:11:39,023
"With your help, which I prefer to think
was accidental, Tom,"

1570
02:11:39,548 --> 02:11:46,387
she has managed to spread bitterness
and troubles throughout this whole town.

1571
02:11:46,388 --> 02:11:49,015
"She has to go.
How do we get rid of her, Tom?"

1572
02:11:49,016 --> 02:11:50,641
"So how do we do it, Tom?"

1573
02:11:50,642 --> 02:11:55,062
"I agree, Tom. You brought her in here.
You got to figure out how to get her out."

1574
02:11:55,063 --> 02:11:57,666
Without her lies
and accusations spreading.

1575
02:12:00,569 --> 02:12:02,879
I asked you here to listen.

1576
02:12:05,866 --> 02:12:08,092
You only came to defend yourselves.

1577
02:12:08,451 --> 02:12:12,930
I'm sorry
it's quite a blow to me...

1578
02:12:14,165 --> 02:12:21,148
"to see all of my friends act this way,
so uncivilized."

1579
02:13:16,850 --> 02:13:20,662
"Your plan didn't work
out very well, did it?"

1580
02:13:21,731 --> 02:13:24,457
"- You'll think of another one.
- No,"

1581
02:13:26,526 --> 02:13:29,671
"No more plans, I promise."

1582
02:13:34,951 --> 02:13:38,137
They asked me to choose
between you and them.

1583
02:13:40,248 --> 02:13:43,769
That's not difficult on a day like today.
I love you.

1584
02:13:44,835 --> 02:13:51,775
"You may be stronger, it's true,
but the ideals, the ideals we share."

1585
02:13:52,885 --> 02:13:58,490
You're exhausted. Lie down.

1586
02:14:05,439 --> 02:14:11,294
"I've chosen, Grace.
I have chosen you."

1587
02:14:15,740 --> 02:14:20,721
Now it is the time!
The time we've been waiting for.

1588
02:14:25,667 --> 02:14:28,310
We free ourselves of Dogville.

1589
02:14:34,634 --> 02:14:41,281
"You're right. You're right, Tom.
It'd be so easy to make love right now."

1590
02:14:43,392 --> 02:14:49,355
They may kill us any minute..
It would be the perfect romantic ending.

1591
02:14:49,356 --> 02:14:52,125
I know. I feel it too. I love you.

1592
02:14:55,737 --> 02:14:58,548
"It would be so beautiful, but from ..."

1593
02:14:59,824 --> 02:15:04,680
"from the point of view of our love,
so completely wrong."

1594
02:15:08,749 --> 02:15:11,936
We were to meet in freedom.

1595
02:15:24,557 --> 02:15:26,950
"You're cold now, Grace."

1596
02:15:36,569 --> 02:15:41,130
I've just rejected everybody
I've ever known in your favor.

1597
02:15:43,366 --> 02:15:45,461
"Wouldn't it be worth compromising,"

1598
02:15:45,462 --> 02:15:48,773
"just one of your ideals
just a little to ease my pain?"

1599
02:15:51,999 --> 02:15:55,352
"Everybody in this town
has had your body, but me."

1600
02:15:56,337 --> 02:15:58,897
We're the ones supposed to be in love.

1601
02:16:01,759 --> 02:16:04,194
My darling Tom.

1602
02:16:07,806 --> 02:16:11,034
You can have me if you want me.

1603
02:16:13,979 --> 02:16:16,539
Just do what the others do.

1604
02:16:17,816 --> 02:16:19,542
Threaten me...

1605
02:16:19,859 --> 02:16:23,035
"Tell me that you'll
turn me in to the law,"

1606
02:16:23,036 --> 02:16:25,808
"to the gangsters, and I promise you,"

1607
02:16:27,033 --> 02:16:30,636
you can take whatever
it is you want from me.

1608
02:16:32,079 --> 02:16:34,140
I trust you...

1609
02:16:36,501 --> 02:16:40,271
but maybe you don't trust yourself?

1610
02:16:40,796 --> 02:16:47,343
"Perhaps you've been tempted, you've been
tempted to join the others and force me."

1611
02:16:47,344 --> 02:16:50,573
Perhaps that's why you're so upset.

1612
02:16:50,681 --> 02:16:53,366
All I've ever tried to do is help you.

1613
02:16:53,725 --> 02:16:58,580
I'm just asking if you're afraid
that you could be so human.

1614
02:16:58,605 --> 02:17:01,542
"No, I'm not afraid of that.
Not in the least."

1615
02:17:02,776 --> 02:17:04,545
Good.

1616
02:17:08,906 --> 02:17:12,093
Let tomorrow bring that it's gonna bring.

1617
02:17:14,579 --> 02:17:20,351
"It's not a crime to
doubt yourself, Tom.."

1618
02:17:22,670 --> 02:17:25,064
but it's wonderful that you don't.

1619
02:17:27,467 --> 02:17:29,610
I can't find the rest.

1620
02:17:32,679 --> 02:17:35,491
Maybe I should go out
for a couple of minutes.

1621
02:17:37,559 --> 02:17:40,120
Take a walk or something...
I don't know.

1622
02:17:42,523 --> 02:17:44,833
To get it all out of my system.

1623
02:17:47,110 --> 02:17:49,212
Trudge the streets..

1624
02:17:50,113 --> 02:17:54,217
Listen to the wind as it passes through
the woods up through the valley

1625
02:17:55,034 --> 02:17:56,677
and all that.

1626
02:18:00,790 --> 02:18:02,558
"You go to sleep, though..."

1627
02:18:06,253 --> 02:18:12,251
You go to sleep
and I will be back very soon.

1628
02:18:20,976 --> 02:18:23,978
Of course it was all a load of nonsense.

1629
02:18:23,979 --> 02:18:29,334
"If anybody was capable of keeping track
of ideals and reality, he was."

1630
02:18:29,360 --> 02:18:35,173
"After all, it was his job.
Moral issues were his home ground."

1631
02:18:35,948 --> 02:18:38,624
To think that he might
doubt his own purity

1632
02:18:38,625 --> 02:18:41,147
was really to think
very little of him.

1633
02:18:41,912 --> 02:18:44,432
Tom was angry.

1634
02:18:46,834 --> 02:18:50,521
"And in the midst of it all,
he discovered why."

1635
02:18:51,088 --> 02:18:54,215
"It was not because of he'd
been wrongly accused,"

1636
02:18:54,216 --> 02:18:57,152
but because the charges were true!

1637
02:18:58,595 --> 02:19:04,410
His anger consisted of a most unpleasant
feeling of being found out!

1638
02:19:07,228 --> 02:19:10,481
It was all quite a blow
to the young philosopher!

1639
02:19:10,482 --> 02:19:12,413
"And realistically enough,..."

1640
02:19:12,414 --> 02:19:17,279
"he thought that if the doubt
was already present, it could grow."

1641
02:19:17,280 --> 02:19:19,429
Perhaps so great that one day

1642
02:19:19,430 --> 02:19:23,729
it would prove detrimental
to his entire moral mission.

1643
02:19:23,869 --> 02:19:26,121
Tom stopped.

1644
02:19:26,122 --> 02:19:31,626
He almost began to shake when the threat
to his career as a writer dawned upon him.

1645
02:19:31,627 --> 02:19:34,865
It didn't take him long
to agree with himself

1646
02:19:34,866 --> 02:19:37,382
that the risk was too great to run.

1647
02:19:37,383 --> 02:19:42,154
The danger Grace was to the town
she was also to him!

1648
02:19:42,220 --> 02:19:44,430
Tom did not like it.

1649
02:19:44,431 --> 02:19:48,618
And he was man enough
to take action to prevent it.

1650
02:19:50,979 --> 02:19:55,694
Fortunately Tom was as conscientious
as regards his future profession...

1651
02:19:55,695 --> 02:19:57,662
as he was practical.

1652
02:19:57,694 --> 02:20:01,947
"He allowed sincerity and ideals
plenty of room in his life,"

1653
02:20:01,948 --> 02:20:05,885
"without getting ""sentimental"" about it,
as he would put it."

1654
02:20:06,661 --> 02:20:10,421
"Throwing away a document
that might be of significance to Tom"

1655
02:20:10,422 --> 02:20:12,954
"and with him
future generation of readers"

1656
02:20:12,955 --> 02:20:15,747
"as the basis of a novel
or indeed a trilogy,"

1657
02:20:15,794 --> 02:20:19,298
"was not an act he was
so stupid to commit,"

1658
02:20:19,299 --> 02:20:24,486
although he had to admit that in a moment
of weakness he might have said he would.

1659
02:20:27,889 --> 02:20:30,460
"Before returning to the
meeting that night"

1660
02:20:30,461 --> 02:20:34,714
"Tom opened the little drawer he
had open the night of Grace's arrival,"

1661
02:20:35,356 --> 02:20:37,498
and found it still there:

1662
02:20:37,732 --> 02:20:40,710
The card from the gangster in the car.

1663
02:21:01,880 --> 02:21:05,734
"The next day the sun was shining
in the brisk autumn sky,"

1664
02:21:05,759 --> 02:21:08,361
and the snow was long since gone.

1665
02:21:10,306 --> 02:21:12,746
For the first time for
ages the pile driver

1666
02:21:12,747 --> 02:21:14,600
could be heard in the marshlands

1667
02:21:14,601 --> 02:21:20,782
as it hammered in the piles for what might
or what might not be a penitentiary.

1668
02:21:21,149 --> 02:21:27,404
"Grace opened her eyes after an almost
unconscious sleep, and was confused."

1669
02:21:27,405 --> 02:21:30,862
"Judging by the light
coming through the cracks in the walls,"

1670
02:21:30,863 --> 02:21:32,575
"it had to be nearly midday."

1671
02:21:32,576 --> 02:21:37,890
"The grey hour as Jack McKay
for some reason called noon in Dogville,"

1672
02:21:37,957 --> 02:21:40,974
"being a man of many
ideas and proclivities,"

1673
02:21:40,975 --> 02:21:45,324
"quite a few of which Grace would
prefer to remain ignorant of."

1674
02:21:46,131 --> 02:21:48,674
But why had nobody roused her?

1675
02:21:48,675 --> 02:21:51,093
Nobody had hammered furiously at her door.

1676
02:21:51,094 --> 02:21:56,449
Not a child had thrown mud into her bed
or broken her remaining windowpanes.

1677
02:21:57,350 --> 02:21:59,685
Now she remembered.

1678
02:21:59,686 --> 02:22:05,124
"She recalled the meeting the previous day,
and puzzled still more."

1679
02:22:05,316 --> 02:22:11,005
Why had she not been confronted with the
outcome of that meeting? Or even killed?

1680
02:22:11,489 --> 02:22:16,260
It was quite unlike Dogville to restrain
its indignation at any point.

1681
02:22:16,368 --> 02:22:19,537
Perhaps things had turned
out well after all?

1682
02:22:19,538 --> 02:22:22,957
"- Good morning, Mrs. Henson.
- Oh.. good morning?"

1683
02:22:22,958 --> 02:22:28,063
I would have come earlier. I overslept.

1684
02:22:28,131 --> 02:22:31,608
"Oh, never mind.
Liz put her back into it this morning."

1685
02:22:32,968 --> 02:22:35,987
We thought some time off
would be good for you.

1686
02:22:39,391 --> 02:22:41,743
That was quite a speech
you made yesterday.

1687
02:22:41,935 --> 02:22:44,495
It gave us all something to think about.

1688
02:22:48,566 --> 02:22:51,252
"- Hello, Liz!
- Hi, Grace.."

1689
02:22:58,367 --> 02:23:00,761
I overslept.

1690
02:23:01,579 --> 02:23:04,997
- Good morning Miss Grace?
- Good morning..

1691
02:23:04,998 --> 02:23:09,086
- How are you this morning?
- I overslept.

1692
02:23:09,087 --> 02:23:11,313
"Oh, that's all right."

1693
02:23:17,178 --> 02:23:20,864
"Tom. Tom, I think it's Grace."

1694
02:23:21,348 --> 02:23:26,953
"Hello, Grace. Two seconds..
Good news."

1695
02:23:35,444 --> 02:23:37,963
I went back to the meeting last night.

1696
02:23:39,698 --> 02:23:42,635
I wasn't going to let
them get off so easily.

1697
02:23:44,370 --> 02:23:47,306
But I'll be damned if the
mood hadn't changed.

1698
02:23:48,499 --> 02:23:50,559
"I wouldn't say we won
exactly, not exactly,"

1699
02:23:50,560 --> 02:23:53,156
"but I think something very good
can come out of this,"

1700
02:23:53,170 --> 02:23:55,379
- something very good.
- Why didn't you come back and tell me?

1701
02:23:55,380 --> 02:23:58,567
"I did, but you were asleep."

1702
02:23:58,925 --> 02:24:01,486
"And you know,
you looked like you needed it.."

1703
02:24:02,637 --> 02:24:05,889
and that made me suggest
that maybe you should have some time off.

1704
02:24:05,890 --> 02:24:10,953
"And you know,
not one single person objected."

1705
02:24:15,067 --> 02:24:16,876
That sounds wonderful.

1706
02:24:16,901 --> 02:24:18,961
"I know it does, doesn't it?"

1707
02:24:19,570 --> 02:24:23,091
The people of this town
they surprise me again and again.

1708
02:24:24,366 --> 02:24:27,910
I might even have to revise
my theories a little bit.

1709
02:24:27,911 --> 02:24:30,514
You know how much I hate
doing that kind of thing.

1710
02:24:32,708 --> 02:24:36,930
"You know, Grace,
last night when I came back"

1711
02:24:36,931 --> 02:24:41,242
"and I saw you
lying there asleep so sweetly,"

1712
02:24:41,508 --> 02:24:47,030
I was suddenly inspired.
I wrote the first chapter of a story.

1713
02:24:47,056 --> 02:24:49,490
A story about a small town.

1714
02:24:49,975 --> 02:24:52,118
Guess where I got the inspiration?

1715
02:24:52,852 --> 02:24:55,955
But I haven't come up with a name
for the town yet.

1716
02:24:57,024 --> 02:24:59,019
Why not just call it Dogville?

1717
02:24:59,020 --> 02:25:00,177
Wouldn't work.

1718
02:25:00,818 --> 02:25:03,111
"No, it wouldn't work.
It's got to be universal."

1719
02:25:03,112 --> 02:25:05,266
"Lot of writers make
that mistake, you see."

1720
02:25:05,906 --> 02:25:08,175
"Hey, do you want me to read it to you?"

1721
02:25:08,659 --> 02:25:11,285
"If there is any love in
it, it comes from you..."

1722
02:25:11,286 --> 02:25:14,306
"Would you be offended, if I said no?"

1723
02:25:15,290 --> 02:25:16,395
"No."

1724
02:25:16,396 --> 02:25:19,779
"If I really do have
the day to myself, I..."

1725
02:25:20,004 --> 02:25:22,522
No. No...

1726
02:25:23,882 --> 02:25:28,319
Two people only hurt each other if they
doubt the love they have for one another.

1727
02:25:30,014 --> 02:25:32,115
You can read it some other time.

1728
02:25:33,558 --> 02:25:37,745
You sit down some place
and gaze out at the mountains.

1729
02:25:37,980 --> 02:25:40,164
It's what the girl in my novel does.

1730
02:25:43,442 --> 02:25:47,171
- I'll see you later.
- I'll see you. Good news!

1731
02:25:52,534 --> 02:25:57,622
"Sensibly, Grace chose to hope
for the best rather than fear the worst,"

1732
02:25:57,623 --> 02:26:01,876
"and planned to spend the day calmly
washing her clothes and herself,"

1733
02:26:01,877 --> 02:26:04,868
"which, for some reason
or another, she was sure"

1734
02:26:04,869 --> 02:26:09,619
"none of the characters from Tom's
fictitious township would dream of doing."

1735
02:26:13,096 --> 02:26:17,241
And then it was
as if Dogville just waited.

1736
02:26:18,226 --> 02:26:23,622
"Even the wind dropped,
leaving the town in an unfamiliar calm."

1737
02:26:24,398 --> 02:26:28,627
"as if somebody had put a large
cheese dish cover over it,"

1738
02:26:29,320 --> 02:26:34,341
and created the kind of quietness that
descends while you are awaiting visitors.

1739
02:26:36,493 --> 02:26:41,252
"After two days off
Grace had been put back to work,"

1740
02:26:41,253 --> 02:26:43,902
"but the quietness remained."

1741
02:26:44,042 --> 02:26:52,009
Indeed it intensified until on the fifth
day it swelled into a strange mood

1742
02:26:53,051 --> 02:26:57,280
"that, all of a sudden, brought all
the citizens to the street to listen."

1743
02:26:59,724 --> 02:27:03,494
"They asked each other
if the phone was really still down,"

1744
02:27:03,728 --> 02:27:07,292
or if they'd heard about Ben
having had to turn his truck around

1745
02:27:07,293 --> 02:27:08,690
on his way to Georgetown

1746
02:27:08,691 --> 02:27:13,253
that very morning on account
of a large tree blocking the road.

1747
02:27:13,487 --> 02:27:15,547
They were not worried.

1748
02:27:15,824 --> 02:27:22,137
"Worried was not the right word,
and then Tom spotted the cars."

1749
02:27:24,081 --> 02:27:26,248
Tom has binoculars.
But you can see 'em with the naked eyes.

1750
02:27:26,249 --> 02:27:27,834
There must be at least eight!

1751
02:27:27,835 --> 02:27:29,543
I thought the road was blocked.

1752
02:27:29,544 --> 02:27:31,939
They must have come through
before the tree came down.

1753
02:27:34,925 --> 02:27:38,695
June's bed! The sheets need changing.
I'll be there in a minute.

1754
02:27:39,596 --> 02:27:40,947
"Hello, June."

1755
02:27:43,182 --> 02:27:47,411
"Grace had just started on the bed,
which June had soiled yet again,"

1756
02:27:47,645 --> 02:27:52,374
when an irritating feeling of wasting
her time forced itself upon her.

1757
02:27:53,484 --> 02:27:56,920
And it was without thinking
she then said the words:

1758
02:27:56,946 --> 02:27:59,381
Nobody gonna sleep here.

1759
02:28:04,286 --> 02:28:06,912
"She didn't say them out loud,"

1760
02:28:06,913 --> 02:28:12,227
but even so she was startled by the
utterance that had urged itself upon her.

1761
02:28:13,879 --> 02:28:17,273
Where had these ominous words come from?

1762
02:28:26,474 --> 02:28:31,454
Darkness was falling as Grace made
her way home from work that evening.

1763
02:28:31,562 --> 02:28:34,309
The people on the square
overlooking the valley

1764
02:28:34,310 --> 02:28:37,192
had finally given up hope
of seeing anything else

1765
02:28:37,193 --> 02:28:39,277
now the light had faded.

1766
02:28:39,278 --> 02:28:42,841
They trudged up Elm
Street in disappointment.

1767
02:28:47,411 --> 02:28:49,036
"- Tom?
- Hi, Grace."

1768
02:28:49,037 --> 02:28:54,059
"There were some cars, but it's too dark,
we can't see any more."

1769
02:28:54,084 --> 02:28:56,978
We haven't seen much of each other.

1770
02:28:57,462 --> 02:29:00,506
"Yah, I know. I've been busy
with my book, you know."

1771
02:29:00,507 --> 02:29:02,400
Can I ask you something?

1772
02:29:03,176 --> 02:29:04,902
"Yeah, anything."

1773
02:29:08,347 --> 02:29:11,325
"You couldn't bring yourself
to throw it away, could you?"

1774
02:29:12,893 --> 02:29:16,455
The number he gave you that night.
You couldn't throw it away.

1775
02:29:16,647 --> 02:29:21,752
I told you how dangerous that man was.
That was stupid.

1776
02:29:27,950 --> 02:29:31,401
"Stupid or not, Tom was soon
a passionate spokesman"

1777
02:29:31,402 --> 02:29:34,357
"for locking Grace
in her shed that night."

1778
02:29:35,791 --> 02:29:40,627
If the vehicles were indeed a sign that
the call Tom had placed five days earlier

1779
02:29:40,628 --> 02:29:42,913
on be half of the
community to the number

1780
02:29:42,914 --> 02:29:45,451
indicated on the card
from his bureau drawer

1781
02:29:45,466 --> 02:29:47,467
"had at last led to action,"

1782
02:29:47,468 --> 02:29:50,721
"and Grace was now to be
eliminated from their lives,"

1783
02:29:50,722 --> 02:29:55,034
it would surely look good
if the town had also locked her up.

1784
02:29:57,103 --> 02:30:01,206
Grace was lying on the bed
when Jason was sent up with the key.

1785
02:30:01,315 --> 02:30:03,900
"Grace heard it turn in the lock,"

1786
02:30:03,901 --> 02:30:08,240
but she was deeply absorbed by
arguments and thoughts on matters

1787
02:30:08,241 --> 02:30:12,269
she had otherwise avoided
for the best part of a year now.

1788
02:30:30,927 --> 02:30:32,915
From the moment when
they'd finally heard

1789
02:30:32,916 --> 02:30:35,347
the sound of vehicles
starting one after the other

1790
02:30:35,348 --> 02:30:37,474
"from the direction of
the edge of the woods,"

1791
02:30:37,475 --> 02:30:40,077
things had moved rapidly.

1792
02:30:40,436 --> 02:30:44,415
Tom had arranged a delegation
to provide a proper reception.

1793
02:30:45,065 --> 02:30:50,587
"Dogville might be off the beaten track,
but it was hospitable, nevertheless."

1794
02:31:03,500 --> 02:31:05,727
Welcome gentlemen. Welcome.

1795
02:31:05,752 --> 02:31:08,253
The town places itself at your disposal!

1796
02:31:08,254 --> 02:31:11,506
I should have a large key to give to you.
But I only have this small one.

1797
02:31:11,507 --> 02:31:13,800
- Where is she?
- Secured by this very key.

1798
02:31:13,801 --> 02:31:15,444
Where is she?

1799
02:31:15,762 --> 02:31:19,014
Okay. If you are wondering
about that sound.

1800
02:31:19,015 --> 02:31:22,475
The driving piles
for the new penitentiary.

1801
02:31:22,476 --> 02:31:25,867
"Tell me, has the crime rate
really gone up in this country,"

1802
02:31:25,868 --> 02:31:27,480
"as we are lead to believe?"

1803
02:31:27,481 --> 02:31:31,170
"Maybe people just
regard things as criminal,"

1804
02:31:31,171 --> 02:31:33,861
"because they envy their success?"

1805
02:31:33,862 --> 02:31:37,758
What's your opinion on the subject?

1806
02:31:38,283 --> 02:31:42,971
Maybe you have none.
I'll get the door... sorry.

1807
02:31:45,541 --> 02:31:48,726
Voila! As the French might say.

1808
02:31:48,835 --> 02:31:50,561
What the hell is this?

1809
02:31:50,879 --> 02:31:52,462
Who did that?

1810
02:31:52,463 --> 02:31:55,233
"Billy, put your hand up,
put your hand up."

1811
02:32:03,808 --> 02:32:06,102
"We felt safer,
when she had the chain on."

1812
02:32:06,103 --> 02:32:09,006
"You are probably more adapted
at handling her kind."

1813
02:32:11,065 --> 02:32:16,528
None of us feel able to accept money
for just helping people.

1814
02:32:16,529 --> 02:32:21,157
I mean not unless it would make you
feel better to divert yourself.

1815
02:32:21,158 --> 02:32:23,593
- Shut the hell up!
- Absolutely.

1816
02:32:28,081 --> 02:32:31,818
"Grace was no expert in
exclusive automobiles,"

1817
02:32:31,819 --> 02:32:34,836
"yet she recognized
with no difficulty..."

1818
02:32:34,837 --> 02:32:38,632
the sound of the vehicle that was
rounding the corner from Canyon Road

1819
02:32:38,633 --> 02:32:39,994
at that very moment.

1820
02:32:41,135 --> 02:32:44,747
"Alas, in Grace's memory
the legendary purr"

1821
02:32:44,748 --> 02:32:49,142
"of the Cadillac series 355C
was inextricably linked"

1822
02:32:49,143 --> 02:32:52,871
"with another,
rather less sophisticated sound:"

1823
02:32:52,980 --> 02:32:57,000
that of gunfire directed
against her person.

1824
02:33:20,882 --> 02:33:22,191
Don't...!

1825
02:33:46,491 --> 02:33:50,553
You need to justify your actions
before you shoot us.

1826
02:33:51,828 --> 02:33:53,930
That's new.

1827
02:33:57,876 --> 02:34:02,146
"That could be interpreted as weakness,
Daddy... I'm disappointed in you!"

1828
02:34:03,089 --> 02:34:04,382
I'm not gonna shoot anybody.

1829
02:34:04,383 --> 02:34:06,651
You shot at me before.

1830
02:34:06,926 --> 02:34:13,032
"Yes, I'm sorry. I regret that."

1831
02:34:13,349 --> 02:34:15,200
You ran away.

1832
02:34:15,477 --> 02:34:19,872
But shooting at you certainly
didn't help matters.

1833
02:34:19,897 --> 02:34:23,166
"Of course not.
You're far, far too stubborn."

1834
02:34:25,736 --> 02:34:28,155
"If you don't want to kill me,
then why did you come?"

1835
02:34:28,156 --> 02:34:30,878
"Our last conversation, the
one in which you told me"

1836
02:34:30,879 --> 02:34:32,866
"what it was you
didn't like about me"

1837
02:34:32,867 --> 02:34:36,413
"never really concluded, as you ran away."

1838
02:34:36,414 --> 02:34:39,915
I should be allowed to tell you
what I don't like about you.

1839
02:34:39,916 --> 02:34:45,855
That I believe would be
a rule of polite conversation.

1840
02:34:45,880 --> 02:34:48,149
That's why you showed up?

1841
02:34:50,926 --> 02:34:53,404
And you call me stubborn.

1842
02:34:53,554 --> 02:34:57,825
You're sure you're not here to force me
to go back and become like you?

1843
02:34:57,933 --> 02:35:01,489
"If I thought there was
a chance of forcing you,"

1844
02:35:01,489 --> 02:35:04,424
"but of course that
will never happen."

1845
02:35:04,731 --> 02:35:12,523
You are more than welcome to return home
and become my daughter again anytime

1846
02:35:13,031 --> 02:35:22,082
and I would even begin to share my power
and responsibility with you if you did.

1847
02:35:23,291 --> 02:35:26,102
Not that you care.

1848
02:35:26,127 --> 02:35:27,728
So what is it?

1849
02:35:28,087 --> 02:35:31,256
"What is it, the thing...
the thing that you don't like about me?"

1850
02:35:31,257 --> 02:35:33,758
It was a word you used that provoked me.

1851
02:35:33,759 --> 02:35:36,403
You called me arrogant.

1852
02:35:36,554 --> 02:35:40,515
"To plunder, as it were, a God given
right. I'd call that arrogant, daddy."

1853
02:35:40,516 --> 02:35:43,768
But that is exactly what
I don't like about you.

1854
02:35:43,769 --> 02:35:45,561
It is you that is arrogant.

1855
02:35:45,562 --> 02:35:47,914
That's what you came here to say?

1856
02:35:51,234 --> 02:35:54,963
"I'm not the one passing judgment, Daddy.
You are."

1857
02:35:55,947 --> 02:36:00,451
"You do not pass judgment,
because you sympathize with them."

1858
02:36:00,452 --> 02:36:07,393
"A deprived childhood and a homicide really
isn't necessarily a homicide, right?"

1859
02:36:07,834 --> 02:36:10,585
The only thing you can
blame is circumstances.

1860
02:36:10,586 --> 02:36:15,507
"Rapists and murderers may be the victims,
according to you."

1861
02:36:15,508 --> 02:36:18,802
"But I, I call them dogs,"

1862
02:36:18,803 --> 02:36:23,097
and if they're lapping up their own vomit
the only way to stop them is with the lash.

1863
02:36:23,098 --> 02:36:25,392
But dogs only obey their own nature.

1864
02:36:25,393 --> 02:36:28,036
So why shouldn't we forgive them?

1865
02:36:28,271 --> 02:36:31,331
"Dogs can be taught many useful things,"

1866
02:36:31,357 --> 02:36:36,711
but not if we forgive them
every time they obey their own nature.

1867
02:36:48,164 --> 02:36:53,418
So I'm arrogant. I'm arrogant
because I forgive them?

1868
02:36:53,419 --> 02:36:54,770
My God..

1869
02:36:54,921 --> 02:36:58,941
Can't you see how condescending
you are when you say that?

1870
02:36:59,301 --> 02:37:03,836
"You have this preconceived
notion that nobody,"

1871
02:37:03,837 --> 02:37:07,932
"listen, that nobody
can't possibly attain"

1872
02:37:07,933 --> 02:37:12,229
"the same high ethical standards as you,
so you exonerate them."

1873
02:37:12,230 --> 02:37:17,400
I can not think of anything
more arrogant than that.

1874
02:37:17,401 --> 02:37:23,697
"You, my child... my dear child
you forgive others with excuses"

1875
02:37:23,698 --> 02:37:26,450
that you would never in the world
permit for yourself.

1876
02:37:26,451 --> 02:37:29,204
Why shouldn't I be merciful?
Why?

1877
02:37:29,205 --> 02:37:34,642
"No no no.. You should be merciful,
when there is time to be merciful."

1878
02:37:34,667 --> 02:37:40,231
But you must maintain your own standard.
You owe them that. You owe them that.

1879
02:37:40,923 --> 02:37:44,401
"The penalty you deserve
for your transgressions,"

1880
02:37:44,402 --> 02:37:47,221
"they deserve
for their transgressions."

1881
02:37:47,222 --> 02:37:48,680
They are human beings.

1882
02:37:48,681 --> 02:37:53,185
No no no.. Does every human being
need to be accountable for their action?

1883
02:37:53,186 --> 02:37:56,062
Of course they do.
But you don't even give them that chance.

1884
02:37:56,063 --> 02:37:58,647
All that is extremely arrogant.

1885
02:37:58,648 --> 02:38:02,127
I love you. I love you.
I love you to death.

1886
02:38:02,402 --> 02:38:06,363
But you are the most arrogant person
I've ever met.

1887
02:38:06,364 --> 02:38:08,675
And you call me arrogant!

1888
02:38:12,662 --> 02:38:16,807
I have no more to say.

1889
02:38:19,544 --> 02:38:23,546
You are arrogant. I'm arrogant.
You've said it. Now you can leave.

1890
02:38:23,547 --> 02:38:26,442
"And without my daughter, I suppose?"

1891
02:38:32,306 --> 02:38:34,825
"- I said, without my daughter?
- Hmm, yes!"

1892
02:38:36,144 --> 02:38:38,894
- Well..
- Yes.

1893
02:38:38,895 --> 02:38:42,945
"Well, you decide.
You decide..."

1894
02:38:42,946 --> 02:38:49,225
"Grace, they say you are
having some trouble here."

1895
02:38:49,823 --> 02:38:54,594
No. No more trouble than back home.

1896
02:38:54,744 --> 02:38:57,246
I'll give you a little
time to think about this.

1897
02:38:57,247 --> 02:38:59,602
Perhaps you will
change your mind.

1898
02:38:59,603 --> 02:39:00,484
I won't.

1899
02:39:00,666 --> 02:39:05,171
"Listen, my love.. power is not so bad..."

1900
02:39:05,172 --> 02:39:11,944
I am sure that you can find a way
to make use of it in your own fashion...

1901
02:39:14,888 --> 02:39:16,990
Take a walk and think about it.

1902
02:39:17,683 --> 02:39:29,110
The people who live here are doing their
best under very hard circumstances.

1903
02:39:29,111 --> 02:39:31,254
"If you say so, Grace."

1904
02:39:32,989 --> 02:39:40,221
But is their best really good enough?

1905
02:39:41,998 --> 02:39:43,307
Do they love you?

1906
02:39:53,467 --> 02:39:56,844
Grace had already thought for a long time.

1907
02:39:56,845 --> 02:40:00,890
She had known that if she were not shot
when the gangsters arrived

1908
02:40:00,891 --> 02:40:04,477
"she would be faced with her father's
suggestion that she return, to become"

1909
02:40:04,478 --> 02:40:07,692
a conspirator with him and
his gang of thugs and felons

1910
02:40:07,693 --> 02:40:09,398
and she did not need any walk

1911
02:40:09,399 --> 02:40:12,169
"to reconsider her response to that,"

1912
02:40:13,070 --> 02:40:16,511
even though the difference between
the people she knew back home

1913
02:40:16,512 --> 02:40:19,117
and the people she'd met
in Dogville had proven

1914
02:40:19,118 --> 02:40:22,386
somewhat slighter than she'd expected.

1915
02:40:23,496 --> 02:40:28,541
Grace looked at the gooseberry bushes
so fragile in the smooth darkness.

1916
02:40:28,542 --> 02:40:32,021
"It was good to know
that if you did not treat them ill,"

1917
02:40:32,047 --> 02:40:37,508
"they would be there, come spring as always,
and come summer they'd again be bursting"

1918
02:40:37,509 --> 02:40:43,264
"with the quite incomprehensible quantity
of berries that were so good in pies,"

1919
02:40:43,265 --> 02:40:45,450
specially with cinnamon.

1920
02:40:47,020 --> 02:40:50,396
Grace looked around at the
frightened faces behind the windowpanes

1921
02:40:50,397 --> 02:40:52,768
"that were following her every step,"

1922
02:40:52,769 --> 02:40:56,471
"and felt ashamed
of being part of inflicting that fear."

1923
02:40:58,113 --> 02:41:02,967
How could she ever hate them for
what was at bottom merely their weakness?

1924
02:41:03,242 --> 02:41:07,013
She would probably have done things
like those that had befallen her

1925
02:41:07,039 --> 02:41:09,623
"if she'd lived in one of these houses,"

1926
02:41:09,624 --> 02:41:13,602
to measure them by her own yardstick
as her father put it.

1927
02:41:13,836 --> 02:41:18,788
"Would she not,
in all honesty, have done the same"

1928
02:41:18,789 --> 02:41:23,830
"as Chuck and Vera
and Ben and Mrs. Henson and Tom"

1929
02:41:24,097 --> 02:41:27,157
and all these people in their houses?

1930
02:41:30,519 --> 02:41:33,080
Grace paused.

1931
02:41:33,355 --> 02:41:38,334
"And while she did, the clouds scattered
and let the moonlight through"

1932
02:41:45,783 --> 02:41:50,137
and Dogville underwent another
of little changes of light.

1933
02:42:03,300 --> 02:42:06,929
"It was as if the light,
previously so merciful and faint,"

1934
02:42:06,930 --> 02:42:11,366
finally refused to cover up
for the town any longer.

1935
02:42:12,350 --> 02:42:14,785
"Suddenly you could
no longer imagine a berry"

1936
02:42:14,786 --> 02:42:17,354
"that would appear one day
on a gooseberry bush,"

1937
02:42:17,355 --> 02:42:20,834
but only see the thorn
that was there right now.

1938
02:42:21,609 --> 02:42:27,093
The light now penetrated every
unevenness and flaw in the buildings...

1939
02:42:27,094 --> 02:42:29,019
and in... the people!

1940
02:42:32,161 --> 02:42:37,224
And all of a sudden she knew the answer
to her question all too well:

1941
02:42:38,209 --> 02:42:44,422
"If she had acted like them, she could not
have defensed a single one of her actions"

1942
02:42:44,423 --> 02:42:47,526
and could not have condemned them
harshly enough.

1943
02:42:48,260 --> 02:42:54,282
It was as if her sorrow and pain finally
assumed their rightful place.

1944
02:42:54,433 --> 02:42:59,537
"No, what they had done was
not good enough."

1945
02:42:59,854 --> 02:43:04,399
"And if one had the power to put it to
rights, it was one's duty to do so,"

1946
02:43:04,400 --> 02:43:08,964
"for the sake of the other towns,
for the sake of humanity,"

1947
02:43:09,822 --> 02:43:15,971
"and not least, for the sake of the
human being that was Grace herself."

1948
02:43:24,336 --> 02:43:30,734
"If I went back and became
your daughter again,"

1949
02:43:31,134 --> 02:43:33,987
when would I be given the power
you're talking about?

1950
02:43:38,391 --> 02:43:41,036
- Now?
- At once!

1951
02:43:41,227 --> 02:43:42,370
Why not?

1952
02:43:48,401 --> 02:43:54,423
So that would mean that I'd also take on
the immediate responsibilities at once.

1953
02:43:55,158 --> 02:43:57,843
I'd be a part in the problem solving...

1954
02:43:59,245 --> 02:44:02,848
like the problem.. of Dogville.

1955
02:44:08,629 --> 02:44:13,692
We can start by shooting a dog
and nailing it to a wall.

1956
02:44:13,717 --> 02:44:17,308
"Over there beneath
that lamp, for example."

1957
02:44:17,309 --> 02:44:20,750
"Well, it might help.
It sometimes does."

1958
02:44:20,932 --> 02:44:24,349
"It would only make the
town more frightened,"

1959
02:44:24,350 --> 02:44:27,131
"but hardly
make it a better place."

1960
02:44:29,232 --> 02:44:31,000
And it could happen again.

1961
02:44:31,777 --> 02:44:42,088
"Somebody happening by,
revealing their frailty."

1962
02:44:48,083 --> 02:44:51,478
"That's what I wanna use the power for,
if you don't mind."

1963
02:44:55,090 --> 02:44:59,319
I wanna make this world a little better.

1964
02:45:03,682 --> 02:45:07,410
"That damn kid won't shut up.
Says he wants to talk to you, Miss."

1965
02:45:07,644 --> 02:45:09,621
Can we just shoot him now?

1966
02:45:11,189 --> 02:45:13,124
Let me talk to him.

1967
02:45:17,612 --> 02:45:19,755
What? What is it?

1968
02:45:22,116 --> 02:45:26,512
"A man can't really be blamed
for being scared now, can he?"

1969
02:45:26,746 --> 02:45:28,806
- No. That's true.
- No!

1970
02:45:29,290 --> 02:45:31,266
"I'm scared, Grace."

1971
02:45:31,417 --> 02:45:34,377
I used you. And I'm sorry.

1972
02:45:34,378 --> 02:45:38,982
"I am stupid, I am.
Maybe even arrogant sometimes."

1973
02:45:41,134 --> 02:45:42,694
"You are, Tom."

1974
02:45:45,138 --> 02:45:49,600
"Although using people is not very
charming, I think you have to agree"

1975
02:45:49,601 --> 02:45:54,479
that this specific illustration
has surpassed all expectations.

1976
02:45:54,480 --> 02:45:56,666
It says so much about being human.

1977
02:45:56,899 --> 02:46:00,350
"It's been painful, but I think you also
have to agree it has been edifying."

1978
02:46:00,351 --> 02:46:01,597
"Wouldn't you say?"

1979
02:46:01,612 --> 02:46:05,591
"Not now, Tom.
Not now."

1980
02:46:09,788 --> 02:46:14,016
"If there is any town in this world
would be better without, this is it."

1981
02:46:20,339 --> 02:46:22,524
Shoot them and burn down the town.

1982
02:46:27,012 --> 02:46:30,115
"What?
Something else, honey?"

1983
02:46:30,974 --> 02:46:33,451
There is a family with kids...

1984
02:46:36,187 --> 02:46:39,373
do the kids first and
make the mother watch.

1985
02:46:39,692 --> 02:46:43,754
Tell her you will stop if she can
hold back her tears.

1986
02:46:47,658 --> 02:46:49,842
I owe her that.

1987
02:46:56,248 --> 02:46:59,518
I'm afraid she cries a little too easily.

1988
02:47:01,754 --> 02:47:04,564
We'd better get you out of here.

1989
02:47:05,841 --> 02:47:09,027
"I'm afraid, you've learned
far too much already."

1990
02:47:15,308 --> 02:47:19,120
"Are you cold, Sweetie.
Do you need a wrap?"

1991
02:47:19,812 --> 02:47:21,122
I'm fine.

1992
02:47:24,275 --> 02:47:27,713
You want the curtains opened?
You don't need them anymore.

1993
02:47:28,070 --> 02:47:29,755
What do you think?

1994
02:47:35,704 --> 02:47:41,767
I think we should open them.
I think it's appropriate.

1995
02:49:38,946 --> 02:49:40,548
"Bingo, Grace!"

1996
02:49:43,117 --> 02:49:44,134
Bingo!

1997
02:49:46,453 --> 02:49:50,349
"I have to tell you, your illustration
beat the hell out of mine."

1998
02:49:52,626 --> 02:49:57,480
"It's frightening, yes, but so clear."

1999
02:49:58,757 --> 02:50:04,529
Do you think that I can allow myself
to use it as an inspiration in my writing?

2000
02:50:13,729 --> 02:50:15,289
Goodbye Tom.

2001
02:50:42,090 --> 02:50:47,070
- Somethings you have to do yourself.
- Really

2002
02:50:50,516 --> 02:50:53,618
That one you're gonna have to explain
to me on the way home.

2003
02:50:55,103 --> 02:50:57,079
Suddenly there was a noise.

2004
02:50:57,104 --> 02:51:02,084
"Not so persuasive and powerful as
it had been on a rainy night in spring,"

2005
02:51:02,109 --> 02:51:06,323
but loud enough to work its way
through the final sighs of the timber

2006
02:51:06,324 --> 02:51:08,225
that was rapidly burning out.

2007
02:51:09,241 --> 02:51:12,594
It came again.
Everyone heard it.

2008
02:51:12,619 --> 02:51:14,745
Grace was the first to recognize it.

2009
02:51:14,746 --> 02:51:16,223
"That's Moses,"

2010
02:51:16,457 --> 02:51:19,643
"That's Moses, she said,
and jumped out of the car."

2011
02:51:20,335 --> 02:51:23,731
"She quickly covered the distance
to the dog pen over what,"

2012
02:51:23,732 --> 02:51:27,425
"now the buildings were gone,
could scarcely be called a street,"

2013
02:51:27,426 --> 02:51:30,523
"and certainly not Elm Street
as there wasn't a tree left"

2014
02:51:30,524 --> 02:51:32,638
"on Dogville's little mountain ledge,"

2015
02:51:32,639 --> 02:51:34,407
let alone an elm.

2016
02:51:34,641 --> 02:51:36,558
It was Moses.

2017
02:51:36,559 --> 02:51:40,079
His survival was astonishing.
A miracle.

2018
02:51:41,230 --> 02:51:44,583
"No, just let him be."

2019
02:51:45,151 --> 02:51:48,379
They will have spotted the flames
in Georgetown by now.

2020
02:51:49,154 --> 02:51:51,507
Some one'll come and find him.

2021
02:51:56,412 --> 02:52:00,015
He's just angry
because I once took his bone.

2022
02:52:10,550 --> 02:52:13,739
"Whether Grace left Dogville
or on the contrary,"

2023
02:52:13,740 --> 02:52:17,014
Dogville had left her
(and the world in general)"

2024
02:52:17,015 --> 02:52:22,412
is a question of a more artful nature
that few would benefit from by asking

2025
02:52:22,437 --> 02:52:25,356
and even fewer by providing an answer.

2026
02:52:25,357 --> 02:52:28,751
And nor indeed will it be answered here!


